node.text:
@mezame.eatanddrink is a natural wine bar which was booked out by @scheong_lai for @upintheairwithme’s birthday celebration. 

Manned by the best friends duo of @lapokku and @dannonxx, the space was small but intimate, reminiscent of the tiny izakayas/speakeasies dotted throughout Japan. 

Appetiser of sweet scallops was followed by a decadent house-made foie gras terrine, and chased with Jamon Iberico with cream cheese on crusty bread.

The Taiwanese-style 卤肉饭 was a delicious tribute to their grandmothers, and the red wine reduction wagyu curry rice was its Japanese-inspired counterpart (imagine 6 bottles of wine reduced to 4 servings of wagyu curry..)

Dessert came in the form of a Hokkaido milk ice cream drizzled with an astringent Greek olive oil and topped with sea salt flakes, fairly similar to what one might find in an Italian mercato.

It was a lovely night with lots of lively banter, brilliant wine and a blast from the past playlist of Chinese karaoke favourites. Definitely looking forward to heading there again soon.
